===Etymology===
{{slim-wikipedia|lang=en}}
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|sofa}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ar|صُفَّة||a [[long]] [[seat]] [[made]] of [[stone]] or [[brick]]}} or {{der|en|arc|צפא}}/[[ܨܦܬܐ]]. Cognate with or derived from {{cog|arc|צפא}}/[[ܨܦܬܐ]] (ṣipā’,  ṣeppəṯā, “mat, matting”). The word may have entered European languages via Turkish or through the Moorish occupation of Iberia.

